Family 1. Euplectellidae. —The spicules of the dermal
                    membrane are “daggers” (fig. l5 a). Examples: Euplectella, Owen; Holascus, E. Sch.;
                    Habrodiclyum, W. T.

Family 4. Aplysixidae.— Canal system diplodal;
                    Collenchyme surrounding the flagellated chambers densely granular. . Fibres with
                    a thick core. Examples: Luffaria, Duch, and Mich.; Vcron-gia, Bwk.; Aplysina, Nardo.

